Mix all of the ingredients together with 1/2 cup (125 mL) of VH(R) Sweet Thai Chili Sauce, reserving the other half for the glaze. Place loaf pan on a baking sheet, pack mixture into loaf pan. Spread remaining chili sauce over the meatloaf. Cook in a 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) oven for 1 1/2 hours, or until a meat thermometer reads 160 degrees F (70 degrees C).